inliner
Class CallbackDescription

java.lang.Object
  inliner.CallbackDescription

public class CallbackDescription
extends java.lang.Object

Description of a callback method to modify. The restrictions are the following:

  • At most two arguments.
  • No primitive types for the arguments
  • return type is void.
The static method called at the beginning of the callback takes the same arguments as the callback (with the callback object itself) and is in the main class of the controller.

Author:
piac6784
